                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, I'm still able to reproduce this issue in 1.9.7.  Here's a test case.\r\n\r\n{code:sql}\r\nCREATE TABLE test (pk serial PRIMARY KEY, testcol boolean NOT NULL);\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n{code:title=Test.php}\r\nclass Test extends Zend_Db_Table_Abstract\r\n{\r\n    protected $_name = 'test';\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n{code:title=testcase.php}\r\n\/\/ ... Initialize things ...\r\n\r\n$test = new Test();\r\n$row = $test->createRow();\r\n$row->testcol = false;\r\n$row->save();\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nResult:\r\n{noformat}\r\nPHP Fatal error:  Uncaught exception 'Zend_Db_Statement_Exception' with message 'SQLSTATE[22P02]: Invalid text representation: 7 ERROR:  invalid input syntax for type boolean: \"\"' in ...\/library\/Zend\/Db\/Statement\/Pdo.php:234\r\n{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexadriaanse",
                        "name": "alexadriaanse",
                        "displayName": "Alex Adriaanse",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-12T13:09:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-12T13:09:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39442",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Reassigned to component maintainer",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-21T10:33:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-21T10:33:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44538",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=vog",
                        "name": "vog",
                        "displayName": "Volker Grabsch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The issue still exists in 1.11.2. The problem is that PDO has different semantics compared to Zend_Db:\r\n\r\n1) The method PDOStatement::bindValue(...) always assumes a string type if the $type parameter is missing, while Zend_Db_Statement::bindValue(...) is expected to determine the database type from the value's PHP type.\r\n\r\n2) The method PDOStatement::execute($params) expects the values of $params to be all strings, while Zend_Db_Statement::execute($params) is expected to use the PHP types.\r\n\r\nThis means that the Zend_Db_Statement_Pdo implementation can only make use of:\r\n\r\n- PDOStatement::bindValue(...) with an explicit $type argument\r\n- PDOStatement::execute() without the $params argument\r\n\r\nThe new patch\r\n\r\n\"Zend_1.11.2_fix_Zend_Db_Statement_Pdo.patch\"\r\n\r\nfixes both issues, so all types including Boolean types will work properly. In contrast to the \"zend_db_explicit_bind\" patches, it only affects the Pdo adapter and does not force all other adapters to use explicit binds.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=vog",
                        "name": "vog",
                        "displayName": "Volker Grabsch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-22T10:11:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-22T10:11:40.000+0000"
                },
